      "BSEE investigation conducted with onsite visits and photo documentation"
    ],
    "summary": "On 25 December 2020 at approximately 18:00, a backfire occurred while attempting to start the compressor engine at MP Block 153 B platform. A sticking fuel valve relay in the pneumatic panel allowed unburnt fuel to saturate the engine, causing a backfire upon the second start attempt. The backfire caused the muffler to separate and become a projectile, damaging wall siding, compressor building lights, crane window, and air filters. No injuries were reported. The platform remained shut in as a result.",
